        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 1:21PM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 121 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Flat Top Mountain, or 17 miles west of Rome, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Burns Junction around 230 PM MDT.
Crooked Creek State Park around 250 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
